Description of 
holotype

. Body dorsolaterally flattened, size small (SVL 
45.50 mm
), tail regenerated (TaL 
31.60 mm
), trunk length (TrunkL 
23.60 mm
), head longer than wide (HeadL 
9.80 mm
, HeadW 
8.50 mm
), eye moderate (EyeD 
2.80 mm
), ear opening oblique (EarD 
0.91 mm
), nare-eye length (NarEye 
3.34 mm
), snout-eye length (SnEye 
4.45 mm
), internarial distance (SnW 
1.70 mm
). Proportions: TrunkL/SVL 0.52, HeadL/SVL 0.22, HeadW/SVL 0.19, HeadW/HeadL 0.87, SnEye/HeadL 0.45, NarEye/HeadL 0.34, EyeD/HeadL 0.29, SnW/HeadL 0.17, EyeD/NarEye 0.84, SnW/HeadW 0.20.

Comparisons. We compare the new species from Hoa Binh Province with other members of the
Hemiphyllodactylus yunnanensis
species group. For comparisons with other species of
Hemiphyllodactylus
see Table 4 .
